  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "\n<p><b>Type:</b> Ninjutsu (Doton)</p>\n<p><b>Rank:</b> 9</p>\n<p><b>Chakra Cost:</b> 12</p>\n\n<p><b>Learn DC:</b> 24 | <b>Successes:</b> 4</p>\n<p><b>Perform:</b> 12 | <b>Perform DC:</b> 26</p>\n\n<p><b>Components:</b> C, H</p>\n\n<hr>\n\n<p>You must be in contact with the surface you wish to affect, or a surface directly connected to it. You can only affect open ground and structures within the area.<br><br>The ground in the area trembles and cracks. Each creature within has a 25% chance to fall into a fissure (Reflex negates). Creatures traveling underground have only a 20% chance to be caught in a fissure. When the technique ends, the fissures close, killing any creatures inside.<br><br>Structures standing on open ground in the target area suffer 100 damage (enough to collapse a typical wooden or non-reinforced masonry building), which ignores hardness. Creatures within a collapsing structure take 8d6 earth damage (Reflex halves) and are @Condition[pinned]{pinned} beneath the rubble, suffering 1d6 nonlethal damage each minute, increasing by 1d6 each minute. If it falls unconscious, it must make a Constitution check (DC 15) each round or take 1d4 points of damage.</p>\n\n\n\n",
